course_metadata.title: Green and friendly house building materials based on waste

content_chunks.content: This digital course is designed to provide knowledge and practical experience in 3 levels (basic, intermediate, and advanced) on green building materials technology, benefits, and properties with a strong focus on the use of waste materials to reduce CO₂ emissions. In this course it will be analysed basics of green building materials; types of waste, that can be used in building materials; safety and environmental considerations, challenges, and solutions in using waste materials for house building materials; criteria of using green building materials in construction; eco-friendly concretes with reduced water and cement content in which some amount of cement or aggregates are replaced by various waste; geopolymers; thermal insulation materials with various waste; composite boards and roofing materials based on waste.

Green building materials technology for waste utilization and CO₂ emission reduction - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in transforming waste materials into sustainable construction resources while minimizing environmental impact. Students master construction waste processing techniques, XRF and XRD analysis methods, and safety protocols for developing eco-friendly building materials from recycled components. The curriculum covers eco-friendly concrete production, geopolymer binder development, waste-based thermal insulation, and composite board manufacturing while addressing material toxicity and leaching concerns. Graduates emerge skilled in implementing waste-based roofing materials, supplementary cementitious materials, and sustainable construction solutions that significantly reduce carbon emissions through innovative waste-to-resource conversion strategies and advanced material characterization techniques.

content_chunks.title: Introduction and Basics of Green Building Materials
Types and Importance of Using Waste in Building Materials
Processing (Collection, Recycling, etc.) of Waste Materials for Construction Use (XRF, XRD, particle size)
Safety and Environmental Considerations, Challenges, and Solutions in Using Waste Materials for House Building Materials (Toxicity, Leaching, XRF)
The aim and Criteria of Using Green Building Materials in construction (properties, sound absorption, durability, etc.)
Greenhouse Gas Emissions Due to Concrete Manufacture

Eco-Friendly Concretes with Reduced Water and Cement Content: Mix Design Principles and Experimental Tests. Waste Materials as a part of binder, Impact on hydration and durability. (Calorimetry tests, DTA, SEM, ASR)
Waste materials as aggregates for concrete (optical microscopy, SEM, density etc.)
Effect of Supplementary Cementitious Materials on the Reduction of CO₂ Emissions from Concrete Progress in the Adoption of Geopolymer Binder (mixing process, strength etc.)
Green thermal insulation materials with various waste (fire resistance, coefficient of thermal conductivity)
